unter poses with a Light Bowgun next to her Palico.\" data-recommended=\"false\" data-hide=\"false\"\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/figure\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003cem\u003eMonster Hunter Wilds\u003c/em\u003e offers up a lot of diverse weapon types to choose from, including the simple Great Sword, the transforming \u003cspan\u003e\u003ca data-ga=\"[[\u0026#34;Embedded Url\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;Internal link\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;https://kotaku.com/monster-hunter-wilds-best-weapon-the-charge-blade-guide-1851769340\u0026#34;,{\u0026#34;metric25\u0026#34;:1}]]\" href=\"https://kotaku.com/monster-hunter-wilds-best-weapon-the-charge-blade-guide-1851769340\"\u003eCharge Blade\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/span\u003e, and a giant music-based weapon known as the Hunting Horn. Two weapons that aren’t quite as distinct from each other are the similarly named Heavy Bowgun and Light Bowgun. What are their differences? And which one best suits your playstyle? Let’s break it all down. - Samuel Moreno \u003cspan\u003e\u003ca data-ga=\"[[\u0026#34;Embedded Url\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;Internal link\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;https://kotaku.com/monster-hunter-wild-heavy-light-bowgun-differences-best-1851773364\u0026#34;,{\u0026#34;metric25\u0026#34;:1}]]\" href=\"https://kotaku.com/monster-hunter-wild-heavy-light-bowgun-differences-best-1851773364\"\u003eRead More\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003cdiv\u003e\u003cfigure id=\"\" data-id=\"30c27cdf1a26323b81eb6b34482890aa\" data-recommend-id=\"image://30c27cdf1a26323b81eb6b34482890aa\" data-format=\"jpg\" data-width=\"1920\" data-height=\"1080\" data-lightbox=\"false\" data-alt=\"A Spongebob SquarePants-themed environment is covered in grime.\" data-recommended=\"false\" data-hide=\"false\" contenteditable=\"false\" draggable=\"false\"\u003e\u003cdiv contenteditable=\"false\" data-alt=\"A Spongebob SquarePants-themed environment is covered in grime.\" data-link-reference=\"\" data-link-target=\"\" data-syndicationrights=\"false\" dat